  "commentary": "With SPX at 6768 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6750 (-52.5B) and positive wall at 6800 (+48.9B), dealers are caught in a high-volatility squeeze where they must buy any dip toward 6750 and sell any push toward 6800, creating whipsaw action in this narrow 50-point range. The BREAKOUT regime with -6.2B total GEX means dealers are amplifying moves, but the proximity to both walls creates conflicting hedging flows that should produce violent intraday reversals. Watch 6750 as the key support where dealer buying kicks in aggressively, and 6800 as resistance where dealer selling intensifies.\n\nBottom line: expect wild swings between 6750 and 6800 with sharp reversals at both levels.",
